         <div type="edition" xml:lang="ocm-Latn" rendition="class:83233 maturity:00000">
<ab xml:lang="san-Latn"><milestone type="pagelike" unit="face" n="A"/><label>Front</label><!-- §5.4. --><lb n="A1"/><g type="ddanda"/> svasti <g type="floretQuatrefoil"/> Om̐ namaś śivāya <g type="danda">.</g></ab> <p>śakarāja <num value="1200">1200</num>
<lb n="A2"/><g type="ddanda"/>di rāja pu-po<unclear>m̃</unclear><!--Le m̃ de po(m̃) doit être mêlé au Om̐ de la ligne précédente. La forme de ce premier m̃ se rapproche du m̃ qu’on voit plus loin à la l. 2.--> tana rayā Indravarmma pu-pom̃ ku ma<lb 
n="A3" break="no"/>dā divyadevī pu-po<unclear>m̃</unclear> 
<!--
En lisant pu-po(m̃) ici, on considère le signe souscrit de la ligne 2 comme appartenant à la ligne 3. Si c’est bien cela, la forme du m̃ (plus semblable à la partie sup. de la voyelle au) est à noter. Serait le seul cas sur cette face ? Mais que faire du u sous le p de pom̃ ?
	sā sidaḥ : cf. C. 92, B1 madā pu põ tana rayā sā sidaḥ yāṅ põ ku śrī sūryyavarmmadeva pu ciy.
Currently, only part of the rā remains at the end of the line, the whole of ja and the -e marker having been lost subsequently to the creation of EFEO est. n. 141.-->
tana rayā nan· sā sidaḥ yām̃ pu rāja⌈<lb break="no" 
n="A4"/>pautra pu-nai sūryyalakṣmī Urām̃ catim̃
<!--	catim̃ : AC-SA face p. 120 lit urām̃ catim̃.
	pāṇḍurāṅgeśa : pāṇḍuraṅgeśa Bergaigne.
	Udbhava: -->
 pāṇḍurāṅgeśa Udbhava di para<lb break="no" 
n="A5"/>ma dvā Amvryak· vijaiya 
<!--	vijaiya pour vijaya ?
	lecture AC, p.76 et 313 PDF : amvryak vijaya dunan saudaryya (beauté) rūpa dunan, (thiu/thau) samastra (tous) sāstragana (traités) dunan. -->
dunan· saundaryya rūpa dunan· thum̃ samastaśāstrāga<lb break="no" 
n="A6"/>ma dunan· dvaḥ karuṇā pu-pom̃ ta<supplied reason="omitted">na</supplied> rayā Indravarmma pu-pom̃ ku nan· dunan· kā sthāpa<lb 
n="A7" break="no"/>nā <supplied reason="omitted">rū</supplied>pa yām̃
<!--	pa yām̃] corr. pu yām̃ (as noted AC, 282 PDF) or rūpa yām̃
AC, p. 282 PDF : dunan kā sthāpanā (ru)pa kamā ka pi kā ātmaja dunan thau samasta bhogopabhoga dunan marai pu (?) cai di pura krauṅ vuk ka põ.
cf. C. 30 B2 line 2 punaḥ sthāpanā rūpa pu pom̃ tana rayā nan·
ka mātāpitā] kamā ka pi kā AC.
-->
 di bhūmi vijaya ka mātāpitā Ātmaja dunan· thu<supplied reason="omitted">m̃</supplied> samastabhogo<lb 
n="A8" break="no"/>pabhoga dunan· marai vuḥ cai di pura kraum̃ vauk· ka pom̃ Ajñā ya śi Ai tuhā
<!--	dunan· marai vuḥ cai di pura kraum̃ : basé sur la lecture d'AC : dunan marai pu cai di pura krauṅ but I read vuḥ cai instead of pu cai. Cf. perhaps C. 120 B4, and vuḥ caittra in C. 43?
	vauk· : AC read vuk·, probalby a simple copying error for vauk·.
 	ka põ ajñā ya çi ai tuhā (AC, p. 282 PDF; 538 PDF); ai (p. 37; 95 PDF).-->
<lb n="A9"/>dunan· ya klan· nagara krauṅ· vauk· <g type="danda"/> jam̃ḥ nan· dunan· marai sthāpanā kīrtti· nim̃ ka pom̃
<!--	dunan ya klan· nagara krauṅ· vauk·] dunan ya klũ nagara krauṅ vok (vauk) (AC, p. 282 PDF), but ya klan nagara kroṅ vuk (AC, f86, p. 144 PDF).
	p. 282 PDF : jaḥ nan dunan marai sthāpanā kirtti nei ka poṅ mahendravarmma ya si ai dunan-->
<lb n="A10"/><!--	mahendravarmma ya si ai dunan (AC, p. 282 pdf)
	sa trā ya sakala senāpatī pāndurāṅgeśa nī mulaṅ di janœḥ dunan rajan samasta (p. 202 PDF)-->māhendravarmma ya śi Ai dunan· sa trā ya sakala senāpatī pāṇḍurā<lb 
n="A11" break="no"/>ṅgeśa 
nī mulam̃ di janam̃ḥ dunan· rajan· samasta dharmma ka santāna dunan· vri<unclear>m̃</unclear> dāna<!--	p. 313 AC: nī mulaṅ du janœḥ dunan rajan samasta dharma la santāna dunan vri (vrei) dāna -->
 tūm̃ yathā<lb break="no"
n="A12"/>śakti <g type="ddanda">.</g></p> <p>nim̃ trā hetu pu-nai harijeṣṭha rājaputrī dunan· si kā svargga nau
<!--	dunan· si kā svargga nau] dunan si kā svargga nau dunan kā sa avan samū (?) dunan dhavek (dhavaik) jīva nau (AC p. 543 PDF)-->
<lb n="A13"/>dunan· kā saqvan· samū dunan· macaik· jīva nau bharuv· dunan· clam̃ṅ·
<!--	or mavaik?
	bharuv dunan· thlam̃ṅ sīdaḥ śarīra ṅan· bhoga dī loka nī : lecture AC p. 269 du pdf. -->
<lb n="A14"/>sīdaḥ śarīra ṅan· bhoga dī loka nī matake Anitya mam̃n· dunan· truḥ
	<!--matake Anitya mam̃n· dunan· truḥ] AC p. 447 du pdf.-->
<lb n="A15"/>samastabhoga dunan· dvaḥ karuṇā pu pom̃ tana rayā Indravarmma 
<!--	samasta bhoga dunan· dvaḥ karuṇā pu pom̃ t. r. : cf. AC p. 282 PDF.-->
<lb n="A16"/>pu-pom̃ ku dunan· nau rajan· tanapaḥ ka Anāk· dunan· tam̃l·
<!--	dunan nau rajan tanapaḥka (=pak ?) anāk p. 481 PDF / dunan nau rajan tanapaḥka (=pak) anāk dunan tœl p. 231 PDF-->
<milestone type="pagelike" unit="face" n="B"/><label>Back</label>
<lb n="B1"/><unclear>tana</unclear>hapa parvvata dunan· paslyam̃ pañce<lb break="no" 
n="B2"/>ndriya sidaḥ k<unclear>ā</unclear>ma-krodha-lobha-moha-mada-
<lb n="B3"/>mātsaryya t<unclear>ū</unclear>y· dunan· strīratnaviśeṣa di loka nī
<!--[a different hand begins]-->
<lb n="B4"/>śakarāja <num value="1200">1200</num>, <gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="1"/> pu lyam̃ surendra Āya dunan· <unclear>ta</unclear>paḥ <gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="3"/>
<lb n="B5"/><gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="3"/> dunan· ma<gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="17"/>
<lb n="B6"/><gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="8"/> nī varunī Ātmaja <num value="20">20</num> thun· jana ||
<lb n="B7"/><seg rend="check">halaḥ jata paṣara</seg> <num value="1200">1200</num>
</p>
